# Public API & Versioning

## mod.ts is the sole public surface

- Every export consumed by hosts must appear in `mod.ts`.
- Internal helpers in `src/` that are not re-exported from `mod.ts` are private — do not rely on direct deep imports from consumers.
- When removing or renaming an export, that is a **breaking change** (major bump).

## Semver rules

| Change type                                    | Bump  |
|------------------------------------------------|-------|
| Bug fix, prompt text tweak, doc update         | Patch |
| New backward-compatible export                 | Minor |
| Removed/renamed export, changed function sig   | Major |

Currently in `0.x` — API is stabilizing. All minor bumps may have breaking changes at `0.x`.

## JSDoc requirement

Every symbol exported from `mod.ts` must have a JSDoc comment. The JSR doc site is generated from these comments.

```typescript
// ❌ BAD
export function ask(...) { ... }

// ✅ GOOD
/**
 * Send a single prompt to the LLM without ActivityWatch context.
 * @param prompt - The user question.
 * @param config - LLM provider config supplied by the host.
 * @param onStatus - Optional progress callback.
 */
export function ask(...) { ... }
```

## Changelog

Update `CHANGELOG.md` for every version bump. Use the format already present in the file — do not invent new section styles.
